#: ../../H/Hanlons-Razor.rst:5
msgid "Hanlon's Razor"
msgstr "Hanlon's Razor"

#: ../../H/Hanlons-Razor.rst:7
msgid "prov\\."
msgstr "ことわざ"

#: ../../H/Hanlons-Razor.rst:9
msgid ""
"A corollary of :ref:`Finagles-Law`\\, similar to Occam's Razor, that reads "
"\"Never attribute to malice that which can be adequately explained by "
"stupidity.\" Quoted here because it seems to be a particular favorite of "
"hackers, often showing up in :ref:`sig-block`\\s, :ref:`fortune-cookie` "
"files and the login banners of BBS systems and commercial networks. This "
"probably reflects the hacker's daily experience of environments created by "
"well-intentioned but short-sighted people. Compare :ref:`Sturgeons-Law`\\, "
":ref:`Ninety-Ninety-Rule`\\."
msgstr ""
"\\ :ref:`Finagles-Law`\\ "
"の系で、オッカムの剃刀に似ており、「愚かさで十分に説明できることを悪意のせいにするな」と読む。ここに引用したのは、ハッカーの特にお気に入りであるように見えるからで、しばしば\\"
" :ref:`sig-block`\\ や\\ :ref:`fortune-cookie`\\ "
"ファイル、BBSシステムや商用ネットワークのログインバナーに現れる。これはおそらく、善意ながら近視眼的な人々が作り出した環境というハッカーの日常的な経験を反映している。\\"
" :ref:`Sturgeons-Law`\\ 、\\ :ref:`Ninety-Ninety-Rule`\\ と比較せよ。"

#: ../../H/Hanlons-Razor.rst:14
msgid ""
"At `http://www.statusq.org/2001/11/26.html "
"<http://www.statusq.org/2001/11/26.html>`_\\  it is claimed that Hanlon's "
"Razor was coined by one Robert J. Hanlon of Scranton, PA. However, a "
"curiously similar remark (\"You have attributed conditions to villainy that "
"simply result from stupidity.\") appears in *Logic of Empire*\\, a classic "
"1941 SF story by Robert A. Heinlein, who calls the error it indicates the "
"‘devil theory’ of sociology. Similar epigrams have been attributed to "
"William James and (on dubious evidence) Napoleon Bonaparte."
msgstr ""
"`http://www.statusq.org/2001/11/26.html "
"<http://www.statusq.org/2001/11/26.html>`_\\ では、Hanlon's "
"Razorはペンシルベニア州スクラントンのRobert J. "
"Hanlonなる人物が作ったと主張されている。しかし、奇妙によく似た言葉(「あなたは単なる愚かさから生じる状況を悪党のせいにしてきた」)が、Robert"
" A. Heinleinによる古典的な1941年のSF短編\\ *Logic of Empire*\\ "
"に現れる。Heinleinはそれが示す誤りを社会学の‘devil theory’(悪魔理論)と呼んでいる。同様の警句はWilliam "
"Jamesや(疑わしい証拠ながら)Napoleon Bonaparteにも帰されている。"
